Reference.Description: Buffer overflow in TFTP client library of CLI

Vulnerability.Title: Buffer overflow in TFTP client library of CLI

cvrf:Acknowledgment.cvrf:Description: Internally discovered and reported by Giuseppe Cocomazzi of Fortinet Product Security team.

cvrf:Note.#text: A buffer overflow [CWE-121] in the TFTP client library of FortiOS, may allow an authenticated local attacker to achieve arbitrary code execution via specially crafted command line arguments.
